1
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:24,980
THE GOOD BAD MOTHER

2
00:00:26,060 --> 00:00:27,440
OH TAE-SOO

3
00:00:27,520 --> 00:00:28,940
FINALE

4
00:00:32,530 --> 00:00:34,110
I'LL BE TAESOCRATES DISSATISFIED
RATHER THAN A PIG SATISFIED

5
00:00:40,370 --> 00:00:41,700
I'm surprised to see you.

6
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:44,080
I heard you were
badly injured in an accident.

7
00:00:44,660 --> 00:00:46,120
I was surprised too.

8
00:00:46,210 --> 00:00:48,120
I thought it was an accident.

9
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:50,210
But it turns out,

10
00:00:50,290 --> 00:00:51,540
it wasn't an accident.

11
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:56,420
Just like how your mistress
Hwang Soo-hyun's corpse was discovered.

12
00:00:57,130 --> 00:00:58,260
Are you here to--

13
00:00:58,340 --> 00:00:59,180
No.

14
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:04,430
I wouldn't have bothered to come here
if I was coming after you.

15
00:01:05,390 --> 00:01:07,850
If a prosecutor
were to leak damaging information,

16
00:01:07,940 --> 00:01:09,690
your opposing party…

17
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:11,610
No.

18
00:01:11,690 --> 00:01:13,980
This entire country would be bent

19
00:01:14,070 --> 00:01:15,900
on taking you down.

20
00:01:15,990 --> 00:01:17,360
Choi Kang-ho.

21
00:01:17,450 --> 00:01:19,490
I'll be straightforward with you.

22
00:01:20,820 --> 00:01:22,280
I only have one goal.

23
00:01:22,870 --> 00:01:23,990
It's to catch

24
00:01:24,620 --> 00:01:27,710
Chairman Song, the man who murdered
my father and also attempted

25
00:01:28,870 --> 00:01:30,710
to kill my mother and me.

26
00:01:35,050 --> 00:01:37,260
I want you to testify against him

27
00:01:37,340 --> 00:01:39,880
regarding all of his crimes
and corrupt deeds

28
00:01:39,970 --> 00:01:41,970
that you swept under the rug.

29
00:01:43,350 --> 00:01:45,810
Then I won't disclose your crimes.

30
00:01:45,890 --> 00:01:47,230
What are you talking about?

31
00:01:47,310 --> 00:01:48,140
Oh Ha-young.

32
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:51,190
She's with me right now.

33
00:02:05,790 --> 00:02:09,710
Her resentment and hatred for you
seem quite deep.

34
00:02:10,330 --> 00:02:12,290
If you refuse to testify,

35
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:15,040
then Ha-young will take the stand instead.

36
00:02:16,210 --> 00:02:18,590
I'm not asking you for a favor.

37
00:02:20,340 --> 00:02:21,760
I'm giving you a chance.

38
00:02:25,850 --> 00:02:27,140
So what will it be?

39
00:02:29,430 --> 00:02:31,520
Will you take down Song Woo-byeok with me

40
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:33,810
and become president?

41
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:36,440
Or will you side with him

42
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:38,280
and go to hell together?

43
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:44,950
THE GOOD BAD MOTHER

44
00:02:45,780 --> 00:02:49,120
Goodness, you're working hard
night and day.

45
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:51,920
Is our food here yet?

46
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,790
HOTEL CAPTAIN

47
00:02:55,380 --> 00:02:57,420
Why did you put it back here?

48
00:03:00,130 --> 00:03:02,510
-What are you doing?
-My gosh, you startled me!

49
00:03:02,590 --> 00:03:04,970
What are you doing to our food?

50
00:03:05,050 --> 00:03:06,010
Give it to me!

51
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:08,560
I was just curious about

52
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:11,390
what people at the Prosecutors' Office
have for a meal.

53
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:14,730
But I guess they're no different from us.

54
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:17,230
Don't tell me

55
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:20,070
you spiked our food.

56
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:21,030
Hey.

57
00:03:21,610 --> 00:03:24,450
Do you think it's that easy to get drugs?

58
00:03:25,070 --> 00:03:27,830
I'd rather spend that money
on buying myself supplements.

59
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:30,370
I haven't slept well
since you guys arrived.

60
00:03:30,450 --> 00:03:32,080
Look at how haggard I am.

61
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,830
Can you tell?

62
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:35,880
You should just quit drinking.

63
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:36,960
Sam-sik.

64
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:38,840
By the way,

65
00:03:40,380 --> 00:03:43,300
is this what people call
an office romance?

66
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:45,890
What are you talking about? What romance?

67
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:51,680
The prosecutor
and his investigation officer.

68
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:57,230
They're on fire!

69
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:02,320
Why are you crying?

70
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:06,570
Next, tell me what you and your dad
talked about on the day of the accident.

71
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:09,080
I'm not sure about this.

72
00:04:09,740 --> 00:04:11,410
What? What do you mean?

73
00:04:11,490 --> 00:04:13,710
Even if I claim that he made me do it,

74
00:04:14,910 --> 00:04:16,170
I have no evidence.

75
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,960
Then I'll end up taking all the blame.

76
00:04:22,550 --> 00:04:24,970
I know I should pay for what I've done.

77
00:04:25,510 --> 00:04:27,930
But I'm afraid
that I may not be of any help

78
00:04:29,350 --> 00:04:30,680
to Kang-ho.

79
00:04:32,810 --> 00:04:35,180
You're already helping him greatly

80
00:04:35,810 --> 00:04:37,520
by doing this.

81
00:04:39,150 --> 00:04:40,820
He said he'll find evidence,

82
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,610
so let's trust him and wait.

83
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:59,460
Song Woo-byeok has ties
with the prosecution and the court.

84
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,000
So it won't be easy to get a warrant.

85
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:06,170
If you attack him
without being fully prepared,

86
00:05:07,510 --> 00:05:09,470
he'll catch on to your plan.

87
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:12,140
And that'll put everyone in danger.

88
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:15,310
When will you return from the US?

89
00:05:15,390 --> 00:05:17,520
If I could,

90
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:20,690
I'd love to stay and watch
the World Series before coming back.

91
00:05:20,770 --> 00:05:24,320
Are you saying you'll neglect
the Woobyeok Beasts this season?

92
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:25,740
You're right.

93
00:05:26,940 --> 00:05:30,410
I must be getting senile.

94
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:40,500
My goodness.

95
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:42,750
What a killer view.

96
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:46,920
I get to see this thanks to you.

97
00:05:49,260 --> 00:05:50,220
By the way,

98
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:52,890
why are you here alone?

99
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,140
Did you have to do that?

100
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:58,310
I devoted my entire life

101
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:00,730
to serving you, sir.

102
00:06:00,810 --> 00:06:02,730
Did you really have to try to kill me?

103
00:06:03,610 --> 00:06:04,650
What are you…

104
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,490
Are you crying?

105
00:06:12,030 --> 00:06:14,870
A grown man crying is embarrassing.

106
00:06:15,370 --> 00:06:17,580
Sir, we should get going.

107
00:06:22,790 --> 00:06:24,000
Hey.

108
00:06:24,090 --> 00:06:26,090
If you made it out alive,

109
00:06:26,670 --> 00:06:30,340
you should've fled
to another country to survive.

110
00:06:30,420 --> 00:06:33,800
Why would you come back here
and drive a nail into your coffin?

111
00:06:34,390 --> 00:06:36,970
In any case, I want to thank you.

112
00:06:37,060 --> 00:06:39,980
When I heard that you were still alive,

113
00:06:40,850 --> 00:06:43,310
I was hesitant about
going on this business trip.

114
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:45,690
But now, I can leave at ease.

115
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:48,690
Goodbye, then.

116
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:54,490
You asked why I came alone.

117
00:06:58,040 --> 00:07:01,080
Mr. Cha will hear
everything you just said.

118
00:07:01,660 --> 00:07:03,040
One of us

119
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:05,290
must stay alive to expose you.

120
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:08,210
You son of a bitch!

121
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,590
You were crying all this time,

122
00:07:10,670 --> 00:07:12,550
and you start bargaining with me

123
00:07:12,630 --> 00:07:15,550
when it's almost time
for my flight, you bastard?

124
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,480
What do you want?

125
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,900
Tell me! You'll be dead soon enough.

126
00:07:25,980 --> 00:07:27,690
Do you need a house? Or money?

127
00:07:28,270 --> 00:07:31,360
Do you want me to adopt you
like I did with Kang-ho?

128
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:34,360
I had the opportunity to farm
thanks to you.

129
00:07:35,490 --> 00:07:37,950
Interestingly enough,
I reaped everything that I sowed.

130
00:07:38,910 --> 00:07:41,080
You'll also reap what you've sown.

131
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:43,750
How dare you?

132
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:45,500
Die, you son of a bitch!

133
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:47,710
-Chairman Song.
-What?

134
00:07:59,180 --> 00:08:00,060
Kang-ho.

135
00:08:03,770 --> 00:08:05,020
You're alive?

136
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,400
My goodness.

137
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:08,860
I don't care about anything else.

138
00:08:10,150 --> 00:08:12,280
I'm completely fine as long as I have you.

139
00:08:15,820 --> 00:08:16,700
I'm sorry.

140
00:08:17,280 --> 00:08:18,570
But I've only just begun.

141
00:08:19,990 --> 00:08:21,040
Song Woo-byeok.

142
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:25,160
You're under arrest for special assault

143
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:26,580
and attempted murder.

144
00:08:26,670 --> 00:08:27,750
What are you doing?

145
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:29,670
You have the right to remain silent.

146
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:32,880
Anything you say can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

147
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,170
Kang-ho.

148
00:08:34,260 --> 00:08:35,380
Will you be okay?

149
00:08:36,680 --> 00:08:38,140
Please don't skip your meals.

150
00:08:40,470 --> 00:08:41,510
Take him.

151
00:08:56,110 --> 00:08:56,950
SO

152
00:08:58,950 --> 00:08:59,910
Hello?

153
00:09:00,490 --> 00:09:02,410
-Hey.
-Let me talk to Choi Kang-ho.

154
00:09:02,490 --> 00:09:03,790
Kang-ho?

155
00:09:04,290 --> 00:09:05,250
Kang…

156
00:09:05,330 --> 00:09:06,540
Hold on.

157
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:09,960
It's for you.

158
00:09:12,170 --> 00:09:14,090
-Hello?
-Choi Kang-ho.

159
00:09:14,710 --> 00:09:15,590
Run away.

160
00:09:16,340 --> 00:09:18,430
It'll be difficult
to obtain an arrest warrant

161
00:09:18,510 --> 00:09:19,840
for Chairman Song's past crimes.

162
00:09:20,340 --> 00:09:22,560
That only leaves us with one option.

163
00:09:23,810 --> 00:09:25,680
We need to catch him red-handed.

164
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:29,190
But I heard he'll be going
on a business trip to the US.

165
00:09:29,850 --> 00:09:31,110
When is that?

166
00:09:31,190 --> 00:09:32,820
Here's the plan.

167
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:35,940
Once I get to the rooftop,
I'd like for you all to accompany me

168
00:09:36,030 --> 00:09:38,360
and carry out a search and seizure
of Woobyeok Group. Got it?

169
00:09:38,450 --> 00:09:39,410
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

170
00:09:39,910 --> 00:09:42,070
Now that he's back,
I'm motivated to work hard.

171
00:09:51,670 --> 00:09:54,210
Recently, a victim claimed to have
received death threats

172
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:56,300
from Chairman Song Woo-byeok,
and thus we conducted an investigation.

173
00:09:56,380 --> 00:09:57,920
And yesterday at 2 p.m.,

174
00:09:58,510 --> 00:10:00,010
we arrested him at the scene

175
00:10:00,090 --> 00:10:02,260
at Woobyeok Group's headquarters

176
00:10:02,350 --> 00:10:05,180
after he assaulted again
and attempted to murder the victim.

177
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:10,060
Since the suspect attempted
to destroy the victim's phone

178
00:10:10,140 --> 00:10:12,770
and was due to fly out to the US,

179
00:10:12,860 --> 00:10:15,940
we deemed it likely that he might
try to destroy evidence and flee.

180
00:10:16,030 --> 00:10:18,280
How will you carry out this investigation?

181
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:19,950
-Sir.
-A civil servant

182
00:10:20,030 --> 00:10:23,490
must be impartial
when serving the country.

183
00:10:23,570 --> 00:10:26,990
As per the Prosecutor General's words
to carry out fair investigations

184
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:29,120
even against the powerful,

185
00:10:29,210 --> 00:10:33,630
we will carry out an honest, transparent,
and thorough investigation.

186
00:10:33,710 --> 00:10:37,380
-What is the victim's current state?
-Did the suspect admit to the charges?

187
00:10:47,060 --> 00:10:48,310
Sir.

188
00:10:48,390 --> 00:10:50,020
It's me, Oh Tae-soo.

189
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:54,730
Young-soon, hurry up. It's starting.

190
00:10:54,810 --> 00:10:55,820
Coming.

191
00:10:58,570 --> 00:11:01,820
When did you enter my heart

192
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:03,950
And make me fall in love?

193
00:11:04,030 --> 00:11:05,200
Come on.

194
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:08,240
-You're…
-My babies.

195
00:11:08,330 --> 00:11:09,660
I brought you some snacks.

196
00:11:11,660 --> 00:11:13,000
Sweet potatoes again.

197
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:14,540
Do you not like sweet potatoes?

198
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,880
Do you want mung bean pancakes?

199
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:19,760
-That's enough.
-Come here.

200
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:21,420
Can we please just watch?

201
00:11:21,510 --> 00:11:25,090
Is that the song that Mr. Baek wrote?

202
00:11:25,180 --> 00:11:26,430
That's right.

203
00:11:26,510 --> 00:11:30,640
Apparently, the song is very popular now.
What was the title again?

204
00:11:31,390 --> 00:11:35,980
-"Intrusion into My Heart."
-That's right.

205
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:38,610
-Come here.
-Goodness.

206
00:11:38,690 --> 00:11:40,150
How nice!

207
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:42,320
You're blocking the TV.

208
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:43,950
This is great!

209
00:11:44,030 --> 00:11:45,530
Let us watch the TV.

210
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:47,200
Hold on.

211
00:11:48,410 --> 00:11:50,830
Move aside! You're blocking the TV.

212
00:11:50,910 --> 00:11:52,330
-What?
-What is it?

213
00:11:52,410 --> 00:11:54,250
-What is that?
-What is that?

214
00:11:54,330 --> 00:11:57,000
Song Woo-byeok from Woobyeok Group
was arrested?

215
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:58,290
What?

216
00:11:58,380 --> 00:12:00,920
Chairman Song has allegedly
engaged in assault and death threats

217
00:12:01,010 --> 00:12:02,550
prior to this incident.

218
00:12:02,630 --> 00:12:06,640
People are in an uproar after learning
that there have been many victims.

219
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:08,760
Recently, a victim claimed to have
received death threats

220
00:12:08,850 --> 00:12:11,430
from Chairman Song Woo-byeok,
and thus we conducted an investigation.

221
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:13,520
What am I looking at?

222
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:15,520
Is that Kang-ho?

223
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:19,610
Can you slap me?

224
00:12:22,990 --> 00:12:25,610
It's him.

225
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:28,160
It hurts, so that must be Kang-ho.

226
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:29,990
It hurts, so that is Kang-ho!

227
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:32,080
Our son

228
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:33,950
Kang-ho is back!

229
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:35,500
Kang-ho!

230
00:12:35,580 --> 00:12:37,080
That's Sam-sik's best friend,

231
00:12:37,580 --> 00:12:39,750
Kang-ho!

232
00:12:40,290 --> 00:12:41,250
What is this?

233
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:44,130
Why didn't you tell me?

234
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:46,470
Did you not trust me?

235
00:12:47,260 --> 00:12:49,140
Answer me!

236
00:12:49,220 --> 00:12:50,260
We're in-laws!

237
00:12:50,350 --> 00:12:51,600
-What?
-What?

238
00:12:52,180 --> 00:12:54,100
-"In-laws"?
-With whom?

239
00:12:54,180 --> 00:12:55,730
With me!

240
00:12:57,350 --> 00:12:59,560
Right, Mother?

241
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:03,280
How about

242
00:13:03,980 --> 00:13:06,570
we all visit Seoul together?

243
00:13:06,650 --> 00:13:09,490
-Sure!
-We must!

244
00:13:09,570 --> 00:13:10,570
Let's go!

245
00:13:11,740 --> 00:13:13,290
Is your seat belt on?

246
00:13:13,370 --> 00:13:15,080
Do you like fish?

247
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:17,290
Feel free to rest your head on this.

248
00:13:17,370 --> 00:13:18,420
Move.

249
00:13:19,830 --> 00:13:21,670
We could've gone by ourselves.

250
00:13:21,750 --> 00:13:23,170
Why is he here?

251
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:24,210
Shut it.

252
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:27,300
If something happens to you on the way,
he'll suspect me.

253
00:13:27,380 --> 00:13:28,630
Easy on the brakes.

254
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:30,760
I just had them replaced.

255
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:34,060
I bought this car to drive
to the award ceremony.

256
00:13:34,140 --> 00:13:37,270
It fits five people perfectly.

257
00:13:37,350 --> 00:13:38,730
You're right.

258
00:13:38,810 --> 00:13:41,900
Gum-ja must've become
a widow for this very day.

259
00:13:41,980 --> 00:13:43,020
What did you say?

260
00:13:43,110 --> 00:13:45,320
I'll buy a bigger car soon,

261
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:46,820
so let's go again another time.

262
00:13:47,490 --> 00:13:48,320
That sounds great!

263
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:50,700
Your son is still considered a suspect.

264
00:13:50,780 --> 00:13:52,660
We still have our eyes on him.

265
00:13:53,530 --> 00:13:54,790
I don't want to hear it.

266
00:13:54,870 --> 00:13:56,500
Just keep your eyes on the road.

267
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:58,080
Yes, ma'am.

268
00:14:02,710 --> 00:14:03,630
Honey.

269
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:05,590
Are you watching from above?

270
00:14:07,210 --> 00:14:08,760
The day has finally come.

271
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:16,470
Our son will carry out the judgment

272
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:20,850
